-- West Ham's Gold Wants Coach Zola to Remain as Coach: Soccer Roundup
-- Alex Duff
-- 2010-04-26T08:56:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-26/west-ham-s-gold-wants-coach-zola-to-remain-as-coach-soccer-roundup.html

          
          
             The following is a roundup of
soccer stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the
Web.  
 Zola’s Reprieve  
 West Ham co-chairman David Gold said Gianfranco Zola
“deserves another crack” at being coach next season after
steering the team toward safety in the Premier League, the Daily
Mirror reported.  
 Gold said Zola “has been through hell and back” in a
turbulent last few months, the Mirror said.  
 United’s Target  
 Manchester United, Ajax and Everton are vying to sign 17-
year-old winger Bob Schepers, the Sun reported.  
 Schepers, who plays for a second-division Dutch team, was
part of the Netherlands Under-17 team that reached the 2009
European Championship final, the Sun said.  
 Liverpool Teen  
 Liverpool wants to sign Charlton’s Jonjo Shelvey for 3
million pounds ($4.6 million) at the end of the season, the
Daily Mail reported.  
 Shelvey, 18, has made more than 40 appearances for Charlton
and can play in midfield or attack, the Mail said.  
 Hull Bank Talks  
 Hull will open talks with banks as it seeks to avoid going
into administration and receiving a 10-point penalty next
season, the Daily Mirror reported.  
 Russell Bartlett, owner of the relegated Premier League
team, hopes that lenders will agree to restructure debt of 35
million pounds, the Mirror said.  
